{{BLP primary sources|date=April 2009}} '''Anne Cofell Saunders''' is an American television writer and producer.
==Biography==
===Career=== Anne Cofell Saunders is currently a Co-Executive Producer on [[NBC]]'s series [[Timeless (TV series)|Timeless]].
She graduated from [[Northwestern University]] in [[Evanston, Illinois]], and earned an MFA in Playwriting from [[Ohio University]]. After teaching English in Japan and backpacking around the world, she started her TV career working on the FOX series ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]'' as an assistant and head researcher. On ''24'', Anne wrote her first freelance TV episode. Shortly afterwards, she was hired as a Staff Writer on [[SyFy]]’s critically acclaimed series [[Battlestar Galactica (2004 TV series)|Battlestar Gallactica]], where she was nominated for a [[Hugo Award]] for her episode “Pegasus" and won a [[Peabody Award]]. Since then, Anne worked as a writer/producer on [[Chuck (TV series)|Chuck]] and the final two seasons of [[Smallville (TV series)|Smallville]]. In 2013, Anne won a [[Saturn Award]] for her work as Co-Executive Producer on NBC's ''Revolution'', which was named Best Network Television Series. Anne Cofell Saunders currently resides in [[Los Angeles]] with her family.
